				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="22-10711_000_041"><a name="22-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote22-10711_000_041">22.</a></span>
					<p>Some are tempted to eat too much. &ldquo;Obesity has reached epidemic proportions globally, with at least 2.8 million people dying each year as a result of being overweight&rdquo; (&ldquo;10 Facts on Obesity,&rdquo; World Health Organization, Mar. 2013, www.who.int/features/factfiles/obesity/en). Others are tempted to eat too little. Anorexia and bulimia devastate many lives, marriages, and families. And some are tempted by sexual appetites forbidden by our Creator. Clarification is found in <span class="emphasis">Handbook 2: Administering the Church,</span> which states: &ldquo;The Lord&rsquo;s law of chastity is abstinence from sexual relations outside of lawful marriage and fidelity within marriage. &hellip; Adultery, fornication, homosexual or lesbian relations, and every other unholy, unnatural, or impure practice are sinful.&rdquo; Still quoting from the handbook: &ldquo;Homosexual behavior violates the commandments of God, is contrary to the purposes of human sexuality, and deprives people of the blessings that can be found in family life and in the saving ordinances of the gospel. &hellip; While opposing homosexual behavior, the Church reaches out with understanding and respect to individuals who are attracted to those of the same gender&rdquo; ([2010], 21.4.5; 21.4.6).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="23-10711_000_041"><a name="23-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote23-10711_000_041">23.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-cor/6.9-20?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1&nbsp;Corinthians 6:9&ndash;20</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/james/1.25-27?lang=eng#24" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">James 1:25&ndash;27</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/130.20-21?lang=eng#19" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 130:20&ndash;21</a>. And we should always remember that &ldquo;men are, that they might have joy&rdquo; (<a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/2.25?lang=eng#24" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2&nbsp;Nephi 2:25</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="24-10711_000_041"><a name="24-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote24-10711_000_041">24.</a></span>
					<p>Mortality is a period of testing, as explained in scripture: &ldquo;We will prove them herewith, to see if they will do all things whatsoever the Lord their God shall command them&rdquo; (<a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/pgp/abr/3.25?lang=eng#24" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Abraham 3:25</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="25-10711_000_041"><a name="25-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote25-10711_000_041">25.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.10?lang=eng#9" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 4:10</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/39.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 39:9</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/15.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Helaman 15:7</a>. <span class="emphasis">Handbook 2</span> includes this message: &ldquo;Homosexual behavior can be forgiven through sincere repentance&rdquo; (21.4.6).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="26-10711_000_041"><a name="26-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote26-10711_000_041">26.</a></span>
					<p>Through the Atonement of Jesus Christ and by obedience to the principles of the gospel, all mankind may be saved (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.4?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 138:4</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.3?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Articles of Faith 1:3</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="27-10711_000_041"><a name="27-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote27-10711_000_041">27.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.33-34?lang=eng#32" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Ether 12:33&ndash;34</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/8.17?lang=eng#16" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moroni 8:17</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="28-10711_000_041"><a name="28-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote28-10711_000_041">28.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/5.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 5:2</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.12-14?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 5:12&ndash;14</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="29-10711_000_041"><a name="29-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote29-10711_000_041">29.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/8.13-17?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Romans 8:13&ndash;17</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/gal/5.13-25?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Galatians 5:13&ndash;25</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.86?lang=eng#85" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 88:86</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="30-10711_000_041"><a name="30-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote30-10711_000_041">30.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/2.27?lang=eng#26" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2&nbsp;Nephi 2:27</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="31-10711_000_041"><a name="31-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote31-10711_000_041">31.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/131.1-4?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 131:1&ndash;4</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="32-10711_000_041"><a name="32-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote32-10711_000_041">32.</a></span>
					<p>&ldquo;The Family: A Proclamation to the World,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign</span> or <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> Nov. 2010, 129.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="33-10711_000_041"><a name="33-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote33-10711_000_041">33.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/19.4-6?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matthew 19:4&ndash;6</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/29.26-27?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 29:26&ndash;27</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/5.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Helaman 5:2</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="34-10711_000_041"><a name="34-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote34-10711_000_041">34.</a></span>
					<p>Each person is born with unique identity, chromosomes, and DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid). DNA is a molecule that encodes genetic instructions used in the development and function of living cells. Each person&rsquo;s DNA is created when the DNA from a father and a mother combine to create the DNA of a new body&mdash;a partnership between father, mother, and child.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="35-10711_000_041"><a name="35-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote35-10711_000_041">35.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/gen/2.24-25?lang=eng#23" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Genesis 2:24&ndash;25</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/gen/3.20-21?lang=eng#19" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3:20&ndash;21</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/gen/4.1-2,25?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">4:1&ndash;2, 25</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="36-10711_000_041"><a name="36-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote36-10711_000_041">36.</a></span>
					<p>Dr. Patrick&nbsp;F. Fagan wrote: &ldquo;The indispensable building block upon which the fortunes of the economy depends [is] the married-parent household&mdash;especially the child-rich family that worships weekly. &hellip; Every marriage creates a new household, an independent economic unit that generates income, spends, saves, and invests&rdquo; (&ldquo;The Family GDP: How Marriage and Fertility Drive the Economy,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">The Family in America,</span> vol. 24, no. 2 [Spring 2010], 136).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="37-10711_000_041"><a name="37-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote37-10711_000_041">37.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/ex/20.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Exodus 20:14</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/lev/18.22?lang=eng#21" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Leviticus 18:22</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/lev/20.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">20:13</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/deut/5.18?lang=eng#17" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Deuteronomy 5:18</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/5.27-28?lang=eng#26" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matthew 5:27&ndash;28</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/10.19?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mark 10:19</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/18.20?lang=eng#19" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Luke 18:20</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/1.26-27?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Romans 1:26&ndash;27</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/13.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">13:9</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/13.22?lang=eng#21" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 13:22</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/12.27-28?lang=eng#26" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3&nbsp;Nephi 12:27&ndash;28</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.24?lang=eng#23" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 42:24</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/59.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">59:6</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="38-10711_000_041"><a name="38-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote38-10711_000_041">38.</a></span>
					<p>See Gordon&nbsp;B. Hinckley, <span class="crossRef"><no-search id="96911_000_020"></no-search>&ldquo;This Thing Was Not Done in a Corner,&rdquo;</span><span class="emphasis"> Ensign,</span> Nov. 1996, 49.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="39-10711_000_041"><a name="39-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote39-10711_000_041">39.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/14.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 14:7</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="40-10711_000_041"><a name="40-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote40-10711_000_041">40.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.39?lang=eng#38" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moses 1:39</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="41-10711_000_041"><a name="41-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote41-10711_000_041">41.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.41,46?lang=eng#40" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2&nbsp;Nephi 9:41, 46</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/16.10?lang=eng#9" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 16:10</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="42-10711_000_041"><a name="42-10711_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote42-10711_000_041">42.</a></span>
					<p>We will be judged according to our deeds and the desire of our hearts (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/137.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 137:9</a>; see also <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/heb/4.12?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Hebrews 4:12</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.32?lang=eng#31" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 18:32</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/6.16?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 6:16</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.109?lang=eng#108" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">88:109</a>).</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
                                        
